This directory contains the Xine 0.5 plugin for dxr3 support
The Xine 0.4.x patches are now located at
http://dxr3.sourceforge.net/download/xine

This is still a work in progress.  Audio output currently does
not use the dxr3 device, although the oss ioctl's will likely be
implemented soon.  dhc is be necessary to switch to 16x9 mode.

You'll need to edit the Makefile to specify your xine src patch and
xine installation path.

"After having installed the dxr3 plugin you must also delete the
corresponding software decoders in the plugins directory. This
is later solved with a priority mechanism (not yet coded).  
(xineplug_decode_spu.so xineplug_decode_mpeg2.so)"

I used:

cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.xine.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/xine co xine-lib
patch -p0 <em8300/xine/xine-lib.diff
cd xine-lib
./cvscompile.sh --prefix=/tmp
make
make install
cd ..

export XINE_CONFIG=/tmp/xine/bin/xine-config
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/tmp/xine/lib

cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.xine.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/xine co xine-ui
cd xine-ui
./cvscompile.sh --prefix=/tmp
make
make install
cd ..

rm -f /tmp/xine/lib/xine/plugins/xineplug_decode_mpeg2*
rm -f /tmp/xine/lib/xine/plugins/xineplug_decode_spu*

cd em8300/xine
make
make install
cd ..

cd modules
./ldm
../scripts/microcode_upload.pl /etc/dxr3.ux

/tmp/xine/bin/xine
